headline: This Beaten-Down Dividend Stock Yields 6.5%. Here's Why It's Worth Doubling Up on in May.
summary: A steep sell-off in the shares of United Parcel Service (NYSE: UPS) has pushed their yield up to 6.5% -- making it one of the 10 highest-yielding stocks in the S&P 500.  Here's why it is failing to deliver for investors, but why the beaten-down dividend stock could be worth buying now.  Consolidated revenue in its most recently reported quarter -- the 2025 first quarter -- was down slightly compared to a year ago.
